{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:john.7",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "John 7",
    "summary": "Source text for John 7 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:1",
      "text": "After these things, Jesus walked in Galilee: for he would not walk in Judea, because the Jews sought to kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:2",
      "text": "Now the Jews feast of tabernacles was at hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:3",
      "text": "And his brethren said to, him: Pass from hence and go into Judea, that thy disciples also may see thy works which thou dost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:4",
      "text": "For there is no man that doth any thing in secret, and he himself seeketh to be known openly. If thou do these things, manifest thyself to the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:5",
      "text": "For neither did his brethren believe in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:6",
      "text": "Then Jesus said to them: My time is not yet come; but your time is always ready.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:7",
      "text": "The world cannot hate you: but me it hateth, because I give testimony of it, that the works thereof are evil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:8",
      "text": "Go you up to this festival day: but I go not up to this festival day, because my time is not accomplished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:9",
      "text": "When he had said these things, he himself stayed in Galilee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:10",
      "text": "But after his brethren were gone up, then he also went up to the feast, not openly, but, as it were, in secret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:11",
      "text": "The Jews therefore sought him on the festival day and said: Where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:12",
      "text": "And there was much murmuring among the multitude concerning him. For some said: He is a good man. And others said: No, but he seduceth the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:13",
      "text": "Yet no man spoke openly of him, for fear of the Jews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:14",
      "text": "Now, about the midst of the feast, Jesus went up into the temple and taught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:15",
      "text": "And the Jews wondered, saying: How doth this man know letters, having never learned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:16",
      "text": "Jesus answered them and said: My doctrine is not mine, but his that sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:17",
      "text": "If any man will do the will of him, he shall know of the doctrine, whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:18",
      "text": "He that speaketh of himself seeketh his own glory: but he that seeketh the glory of him that sent him, he is true and there is no injustice in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:19",
      "text": "Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keepeth the law?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:20",
      "text": "Why seek you to kill me? The multitude answered and said: Thou hast a devil. Who seeketh to kill thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:21",
      "text": "Jesus answered and said to them: One work I have done: and you all wonder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:22",
      "text": "Therefore, Moses gave you circumcision (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers): and on the sabbath day you circumcise a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:23",
      "text": "If a man receive circumcision on the sabbath day, that the law of Moses may not be broken: are you angry at me, because I have healed the whole man on the sabbath day?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:24",
      "text": "Judge not according to the appearance: but judge just judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:25",
      "text": "Some therefore of Jerusalem said: Is not this he whom they seek to kill?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:26",
      "text": "And behold, he speaketh openly: and they say nothing to him. Have the rulers known for a truth that this is the Christ?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:27",
      "text": "But we know this man, whence he is: but when the Christ cometh, no man knoweth, whence he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:28",
      "text": "Jesus therefore cried out in the temple, teaching and saying: You both know me, and you know whence I am. And I am not come of myself: but he that sent me is true, whom you know not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:29",
      "text": "I know him, because I am from him: and he hath sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:30",
      "text": "They sought therefore to apprehend him: and no man laid hands on him, because his hour was not yet come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:31",
      "text": "But of the people many believed in him and said: When the Christ cometh, shall he do more miracles than this man doth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:32",
      "text": "The Pharisees heard the people murmuring these things concerning him: and the rulers and Pharisees sent ministers to apprehend him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:33",
      "text": "Jesus therefore said to them: Yet a little while I am with you: and then I go to him that sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:34",
      "text": "You shall seek me and shall not find me: and where I am, thither you cannot come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:35",
      "text": "The Jews therefore said among themselves: Whither will he go, that we shall not find him? Will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles and teach the Gentiles?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:36",
      "text": "What is this saying that he hath said: You shall seek me and shall not find me? And: Where I am, you cannot come?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:37",
      "text": "And on the last, and great day of the festivity, Jesus stood and cried, saying: If any man thirst, let him come to me and drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:38",
      "text": "He that believeth in me, as the scripture saith: Out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:39",
      "text": "Now this he said of the Spirit which they should receive who believed in him: for as yet the Spirit was not given, because Jesus was not yet glorified.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:40",
      "text": "Of that multitude therefore, when they had heard these words of his, some said: This is the prophet indeed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:41",
      "text": "Others said: This is the Christ. But some said: Doth the Christ come out of Galilee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:42",
      "text": "Doth not the scripture say: That Christ cometh of the seed of David and from Bethlehem the town where David was?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:43",
      "text": "So there arose a dissension among the people because of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:44",
      "text": "And some of them would have apprehended him: but no man laid hands upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:45",
      "text": "The ministers therefore came to the chief priests and the Pharisees. And they said to them: Why have you not brought him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.46",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:46",
      "text": "The ministers answered: Never did man speak like this man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.47",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:47",
      "text": "The Pharisees therefore answered them: Are you also seduced?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.48",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:48",
      "text": "Hath any one of the rulers believed in him, or of the Pharisees?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.49",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:49",
      "text": "But this multitude, that knoweth not the law, are accursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.50",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:50",
      "text": "Nicodemus said to them (he that came to him by night, who was one of them):",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.51",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:51",
      "text": "Doth our law judge any man, unless it first hear him and know what he doth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.52",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:52",
      "text": "They answered and said to him: Art thou also a Galilean? Search the scriptures, and see that out of Galilee a prophet riseth not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.7.53",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:53",
      "text": "And every man returned to his own house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
